commit.message:
BF: fix quaternion norm

Thanks to Maxime Lemonnier for pointing out that I was returning the
squared norm.

MAINT: refactor travis script

Refactor for clarity.

TST: set up testing with py.test and nose

Set up travis options to test with nose and py.test.

We can drop the nose testing soon.

RF: move to testing with pytest

Refactor tests to use pytest idioms.

Testing should work with both pytest and nose, at least for now.

TST: adapt doctests to new numpy output format

Numpy 1.14 has a different array repr; adapt tests to that.

MAINT: update to latest transformations.py

Closes gh-15 - thanks to Samuel John for reminding me.

DOC: rewrite mat2quat docstring

Move main part of notes to top of docstring.

MAINT: refactor, expand travis testing

Add Python 3.6.  Refactor to use ordinary wheels.
MAINT: release updates

RF: add top-level module imports for all modules

Fixes gh-13.

DOC: update release instructions

Doc build and upload.

Uploading signed wheels via twine.

MAINT: allow travis to install from pypi

Allow packages from pypi index as well as travis wheelhouse.
